-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Specifically, "the numerical measure of temper=
ature shall be simply the mechanical equivalent of the thermal unit divided=
 by Carnot's function."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEThomson1882234_30-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kelvin#cite_note-=
FOOTNOTEThomson1882234-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>30<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>To explain this definition, consider a reversible <a href=3D"https:/=
